Overview: 
This is a continuation of the first Security Engineer Homelab. After going through the steps of hardening my first Ubuntu server I wanted this project to be a step above. 
For my previous project (Intro Web Pentesting Lab), I went through the steps of a beginner red team web tester and for this project I want to be able to defend against those type of attacks. 
For this project, my goal is to have an ubuntu server and set up detection for brute force attempts, privilege escalation attempts, unauthorized creation attempts, etc. 
Once these detections are in place I want to send all logs and alerts into another VM that has Wazuh to have a visulazation of all the information.  
Finally, after creating the detection for these attempts, I want to test that the rules are working in place by attacking using my Kali VM and documenting the process. 

